    "body": "Currently `da.histogram` is unable to handle the case where `range` is not specified or for that matter when `range` consists of lazy values. It would be nice for `da.histogram` to handle this case by simply using the min/max of the data as the default `range` (as is done in `np.histogram`). Further it would be good if `da.histogram` avoided (accidentally) computing lazy values used for the `range`.",
